  "prompt": "How do I get a job in US?",
  "response": "To get a job in the US, follow these steps:\n\n1. Legal Work Authorization\n- Have a valid work visa or green card\n- Common visa types: H-1B, L-1, J-1, TN, O-1\n- Ensure you're legally allowed to work in the US\n\n2. Job Search Strategies\n- Update your resume/CV (US-style)\n- Use job search websites:\n  - LinkedIn\n  - Indeed\n  - Glassdoor\n  - Monster\n- Network professionally\n- Attend job fairs\n- Use professional connections\n\n3. Qualifications\n- Ensure your educational credentials are recognized\n- Get certifications if needed\n- Improve English language skills\n- Understand US job market expectations\n\n4. Application Process\n- Customize resume for each job\n- Write compelling cover letters\n- Prepare for interviews\n- Be ready for virtual/in-person interviews\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Research potential employers\n- Consider recruitment agencies\n- Build a professional online presence\n- Be persistent and patient\n\n6. Specific Fields\n- Some industries (tech, healthcare) are more open to international workers\n- Research industry-specific requirements\n\nRemember that competition can be high, so preparation and persistence are key.",
